    h2 Dog Behaviour when lost
    p Man's best friend, our ever-lovable 4 legged companions. Whenever dogs go missing, they will wander around in search of things that interest them or
    p for their owner. This is typically the easiest time to find and retrieve the dog, as they will respond to commands and sounds/smells they recognize.
    p Depending on the species/treatment a dog has received, after an hour or week dogs will switch to a "survival" mode and default to most of their primal
    p survival instincts. They will become wary of humans and will only seek food, water, and safety. They will also ignore commands they were trained to
    p heed and toys they've played with for years as this survival mode suppresses their pet personality.
    h2 How to properly retrieve a lost dog
    p To properly retrieve a dog, set up a trap with food dogs like or water. If you yourself are not the owner, this method must be used, as other
    p methods will not work and chasing down the dog will stress it out and kick survival mode into overdrive.
    p If you are the dog's owner, you may attempt to try to get it to recognize you by slowly gaining its trust through food until the recognize you.
    p Survival mode usually ends shortly after recognizing their owner.
